claim.claim-text:
A system (10) comprising:
a thrust system (24) that includes at least one electromechanical actuator for controlling a thrust vector of the thrust system;
a generator (16) for providing electric power to the at least one electromechanical actuator of the thrust system;
a turbine (14) for driving the generator;
a speed control valve (20) for metering propellant to the turbine; and
a gear assembly (18) for connecting the turbine, the generator, and the speed control valve.

The system of claim 1, wherein the gear assembly (18) comprises:
a spur gear (52) engaged to the turbine (14);
a first intermediate gear (54) engaged with the spur gear (52);
a second intermediate gear (56) engaged with the first intermediate gear (54) and the generator (16);
a third intermediate gear (80) engaged with the first intermediate gear (54); and
an output gear (58) engaged to the third intermediate gear and the speed control valve (20).

A method for providing thrust to a space launch vehicle, the method comprising:
providing propellant to a turbine (14) through a speed control valve (20);
powering a gear assembly (18) using the turbine (14);
powering a generator (16) using the gear assembly (18), wherein the generator (16) provides electric power to a thrust system (24);
powering the speed control valve (20) using the gear assembly (18); and
electromechanically controlling a thrust vector of the thrust system (24).

The method of claim 5, wherein powering a gear assembly comprises:
powering a spur gear (52) using the turbine (14);
powering a first intermediate gear (54) using the spur gear (52);
powering second (56) and third (80) intermediate gears using the first intermediate gear (54);
powering a speed control output gear (58) using the second intermediate gear (56); and
powering a generator output gear using the third intermediate gear.

A turbine generator assembly (12), the system comprising:
a generator (16) for providing electric power to a thrust vector control system;
a turbine (14) for driving the generator;
a speed control valve (20) for controlling propellant to the turbine (14); and
a gear assembly for connecting the turbine, the generator, and the speed control valve.

The assembly of claim 10, wherein the gear assembly comprises:
a spur gear (52) engaged to the turbine (14);
a first intermediate gear (54) engaged with the spur gear;
a second intermediate gear (56) engaged with the first intermediate gear (54) and the generator (16);
a third intermediate gear (80) engaged with the first intermediate gear (54); and
an output gear (58) engaged to the third intermediate gear (80) and the speed control valve (20).
